<br>
Heres an example.  You raid 20 hours a week.   There is a couple (either boyfriend/girlfriend or husband/wife) that takes turns 2-boxing each other.  Both raid 12 hours a week.  Even though you raid more than either one, you get less consideration then them because each of their characters are in attendance 24 hours (2 players boxing 2 chars for 12 hours a week = 24 hours per char).<br>
<br>
I must say there is no perfect loot system.   Merit is very subjective and there are instances where loot is given to favorites first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=triggersite>Triggersite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/13/03 8:17:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25954.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wingedascension.com/pictures/small/Triggersite.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you use DKP?</span><hr size=1> I'm not high enough to raid like that, but I don't see the conflict with 2-boxing.<br>
